author: Florence Nightingale

title: Charles Dickens (1812-70)

author: Charles Dickens (1812-70)

author: Charles Dickens (1812-70)

quote: It was as true as taxes is.  And nothing's truer than them.
author: Charles Dickens (1812-70)

quote: Assassination is the extreme form of censorship.

quote: In Heaven an angel is nobody in particular.

quote: Man can climb to the highest summits, but he cannot dwell there long.

quote: My spelling is Wobbly.  It's good spelling but it Wobbles, and the letters get in the wrong places.
author: A. A. Milne (1882-1958)
